    <!-- Headline/author/sponsor -->
    <header>
      <h1>48 Reporters Asked This Guy The Same Dumb Question About Women. His Response? Absolutely Perfect.</h1>
        <address> Curated by <a href="/adam-mordecai" class="name analytic_event" data-ga-action="More From Curator" data-ga-category="Nugget" data-ga-label="pageTitle" rel="author">Adam Mordecai</a>
        </address>
    </header>


    <div id="lede">
      <p>Joss Whedon, director of "The Avengers" and the creator of some of my favorite shows ever, has a history of writing strong women characters. Back in 2006, the organization Equality Now honored him for being a staunch ally for women. In his thank-you speech, he decided to talk about the tedious and vapid question journalists never stop asking him. At 6:25, I thought he nailed everything wrong with our culture, but then he takes it to the next level at 6:50 and hammers home the horrible reality.</p>
    </div>

